  "prompt": "What universities does Viad recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Viad is known for recruiting new graduates from a diverse range of universities, particularly those that offer strong programs aligned with their industry needs. While the specific universities and preferred majors can vary based on the region and the specific roles available at any given time, here's a general overview:\n\n### **Universities**\nViad typically targets universities that have robust programs in areas relevant to their business operations. These may include:\n\n- **Top Public and Private Universities:** Institutions renowned for their engineering, business, computer science, and other related programs.\n- **Specialized Institutes:** Universities that offer specialized courses or have strong industry connections in fields pertinent to Viad\u2019s operations.\n- **Regional Universities:** Depending on Viad\u2019s geographic presence, they may also recruit from prominent local universities to tap into regional talent pools.\n\nSome examples (note that this is a general assumption and may vary):\n\n- **United States:** Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), Stanford University, University of California\u2013Berkeley, Georgia Institute of Technology, University of Michigan.\n- **United Kingdom:** Imperial College London, University of Cambridge, University of Oxford, University College London.\n- **Canada:** University of Toronto, University of British Columbia, McGill University.\n- **Australia:** University of Melbourne, University of Sydney, Australian National University.\n\n### **Majors**\nViad looks for candidates with academic backgrounds that match the roles they are hiring for. Common majors include:\n\n- **Engineering:** Civil, Mechanical, Electrical, Software, and Industrial Engineering.\n- **Computer Science & Information Technology:** Software Development, Data Science, Information Systems.\n- **Business & Finance:** Business Administration, Finance, Marketing, Economics.\n- **Design & Architecture:** Industrial Design, Architecture, Urban Planning.\n- **Environmental Sciences:** Environmental Engineering, Sustainability Studies.\n- **Other Relevant Fields:** Project Management, Supply Chain Management, Communications.\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n- **Internships and Practical Experience:** Viad often values candidates who have practical experience through internships, co-op programs, or projects relevant to their field.\n- **Soft Skills:** Strong communication, teamwork, problem-solving abilities, and adaptability are highly sought after.\n- **Certifications:** Depending on the role, certain certifications may be advantageous (e.g., PMP for project management roles, specific software proficiencies for technical positions).\n\n### **Next Steps**\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding Viad\u2019s recruitment process, preferred universities, and desired majors, consider the following:\n\n1. **Visit Viad\u2019s Official Careers Page:** Companies often list their recruitment partners, upcoming job fairs, and specific role requirements on their websites.\n2. **Attend Career Fairs and Networking Events:** These events provide direct interaction opportunities with Viad\u2019s recruitment team.\n3. **Connect on Professional Platforms:** Platforms like LinkedIn can offer insights into the backgrounds of current Viad employees and the types of universities and majors they come from.\n4. **Reach Out Directly:** Contact Viad\u2019s HR or recruitment department for specific inquiries about their hiring criteria and processes.\n\nBy staying proactive and leveraging available resources, you can better align your educational background and career aspirations with Viad\u2019s recruitment preferences.",
